abstract: A full year before Election Day 2020, Republicans quietly executed a “dry run” of President Donald Trump's massive reelection machine.
snippet: A full year before Election Day 2020, Republicans quietly executed a “dry run” of President Donald Trump's massive reelection machine.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — A full year before Election Day 2020, Republicans quietly executed a “dry run” of President Donald Trump's massive reelection machine.
headline_main: A Free Pass for Trump? GOP Presses Edge in Key Battlegrounds
headline_print_headline: A Free Pass for Trump? GOP Presses Edge in Key Battlegrounds

abstract: Democratic presidential contender Elizabeth Warren defended her Medicare for All healthcare proposal on Monday, telling members of an influential Nevada labor union that she wants all Americans to have coverage that is as good as theirs.
snippet: Democratic presidential contender Elizabeth Warren defended her Medicare for All healthcare proposal on Monday, telling members of an influential Nevada labor union that she wants all Americans to have coverage that is as good as theirs.
lead_paragraph: LAS VEGAS — Democratic presidential contender Elizabeth Warren defended her Medicare for All healthcare proposal on Monday, telling members of an influential Nevada labor union that she wants all Americans to have coverage that is as good as theirs.
headline_main: Warren Woos Nevada Union Amid Healthcare Policy Concerns
headline_print_headline: Warren Woos Nevada Union Amid Healthcare Policy Concerns

abstract: House Democrats announced two articles of impeachment against President Donald Trump, declaring he “betrayed the nation” with his actions toward Ukraine as they pushed toward historic proceedings that are certain to help define his presidency and shape the 2020 election.
snippet: House Democrats announced two articles of impeachment against President Donald Trump, declaring he “betrayed the nation” with his actions toward Ukraine as they pushed toward historic proceedings that are certain to help define his presidency and ...
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — House Democrats announced two articles of impeachment against President Donald Trump, declaring he “betrayed the nation” with his actions toward Ukraine as they pushed toward historic proceedings that are certain to help define his presidency and shape the 2020 election.
headline_main: Democrats' Impeachment Charges Say Trump Betrayed the Nation
headline_print_headline: Democrats' Impeachment Charges Say Trump Betrayed the Nation

abstract: The former Trump deputy campaign chairman pleaded guilty to fraud and lying to prosecutors, but his lawyers said his cooperation in the Russia inquiry and others should reduce his sentence.
snippet: The former Trump deputy campaign chairman pleaded guilty to fraud and lying to prosecutors, but his lawyers said his cooperation in the Russia inquiry and others should reduce his sentence.
lead_paragraph: Lawyers for President Trump’s former deputy campaign chairman argued in a court filing late Monday that he should be spared prison time for his crimes because he cooperated extensively with prosecutors investigating Russia’s efforts to sway the 2016 presidential election and other matters.

snippet: Pierce Bush is running in the 22nd House District, and Ronny L. Jackson is running in the 13th District.
lead_paragraph: One comes from a political dynasty that has had its differences with President Trump, and the other is intertwined with the president. Now, both are seeking to fill a Republican power vacuum in open-seat congressional races in Texas.

abstract: The Journal-Constitution threatened legal action over the Clint Eastwood movie’s depiction of its 1996 Olympic bomb reporting.
snippet: The Journal-Constitution threatened legal action over the Clint Eastwood movie’s depiction of its 1996 Olympic bomb reporting.
lead_paragraph: A war of words erupted on Monday between The Atlanta Journal-Constitution and Warner Bros. over “Richard Jewell,” a new Clint Eastwood-directed film that depicts the newspaper’s reporting after a bomb exploded at the 1996 Summer Olympics.

abstract: U.S. lawmakers announced an agreement on Monday on a $738-billion bill setting policy for the Department of Defense, including new measures for competing with Russia and China, family leave for federal workers and the creation of President Donald Trump's long-desired Space Force.
snippet: U.S. lawmakers announced an agreement on Monday on a $738-billion bill setting policy for the Department of Defense, including new measures for competing with Russia and China, family leave for federal workers and the creation of President Donald ...
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — U.S. lawmakers announced an agreement on Monday on a $738-billion bill setting policy for the Department of Defense, including new measures for competing with Russia and China, family leave for federal workers and the creation of President Donald Trump's long-desired Space Force.
headline_main: U.S. Lawmakers Reach Deal on Massive Defense Bill, Eye Russia, Turkey, China
headline_print_headline: U.S. Lawmakers Reach Deal on Massive Defense Bill, Eye Russia, Turkey, China

abstract: As President Trump faces impeachment by the House, it is the very concept of truth that often seems to be on trial.
